<h2>Now</h2>
<p>
    I build AI tooling for internal teams in pharma, and I'm learning a bit
    about CUDA and performance engineering in my spare time. I also help run Baileys
    Analytics, a small analytics platform for vacation rentals.
</p>
<p>
I post ad hoc updates to my <a href="/now">now page</a>.
</p>
<h2>Studies</h2>
<p>
    I graduated from the <a href="/writing/my-wisconsin-experience/">University of Wisconsin-Madison</a> in 2026 with a B.S. in Computer Sciences and Data Science. I spent most of my time hanging out in the
    <a href="https://www.upl.cs.wisc.edu/" target="_blank">UPL</a> on campus with my <a href="/friends">friends</a>.
</p>
<p>
    For two years, I was a member of the <a href="https://skunkworks.engr.wisc.edu/" target="_blank">Informatics Skunkworks</a> research group, led by Dr. Dane Morgan, where I trained generative models to design new crystal structures with target physical properties. I helped found the <a href="https://wqi.wisc.edu/wqcc/" target="_blank">Wisconsin Quantum Computing Club</a> as one of its first four officers, and later competed with the group at MIT's IQuHACK. At the UPL, I served as a lab coordinator, introduced its Lightning Talks, and helped organize <a href="https://www.madhacks.io/" target="_blank">MadHacks</a>, growing it to a record 417 participants.
</p>

<h2>Colophon</h2>
<p>
    This site is built with <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/" target="_blank">Eleventy</a>, HTML, and CSS. No JavaScript by default; posts that need it pull in MathJax, a table of contents, sidenotes, or category filters. Images are converted to AVIF at build time, and links prefetch on hover via <a href="https://instant.page/" target="_blank">instant.page</a>. There's an <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> and a <a href="/sitemap.xml">sitemap</a>.
</p>
<p>Source <a href="https://github.com/nicosalm/salm.dev/" target="_blank">on GitHub</a>.</p>

